nto every piece she creates. Her collaboration with Lany Space brings her signature colorful, playful style into the world of designer rugs.<br><br>In this interview, Darra shares the story behind her creative journey and how her unique designs came to life with Lany Space. </p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-6e57" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dJjagV cQqdEF pf-23_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-kCMLfs khbiTF"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-24_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-25_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/files/d0a3a2e1123b29cc92c6e1080dcea83b.webp?v=1747972415" width="1500" height="1000" alt="Designer: Darra Sargnt" title="Designer: Darra Sargnt" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-eoVZcn jdMidl pf-26_ pf-image-1"/><h4 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-27_"><em><strong>Designer: Darra Sargent · IG:&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://www.instagram.com/deardarlingdesignstudio/" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(1, 126, 86);">@deardarlingdesignstudio</span></a></strong></em></h4></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-cf4b" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dJjagV cQqdEF pf-29_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-kCMLfs khbiTF"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-30_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-31_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-32_ pf-heading-1-h2"><i class="sc-czkhzk fzclRt pf-33_ pf-icon-1 pfa pfa-star pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide pf-hide" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>An Interview with Darra Sargent </h2></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-34_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-35_"><p class="sc-knuQPt cmQWaw pf-36_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><em><strong>Q: Hello  Darra, how would you describe your design style?</strong></em><strong><br><br></strong>My design style is heavily influenced by design of the past! I love creating work inspired by different decades in design, but my personal favorite decades are the 1960s and 70s. I try to bring the feeling that design had during that era to a modern audience. Color is the most important part of art in my opinion and I love including a rainbow of some kind in every one of my pieces as my little signature touch. My go-to color palettes are also heavily influenced by vintage home decor and fashion. I'd say overall my style is vintage inspired, colorful art to make you feel groovy. <strong><br><br><em>Q:&nbsp;How have your personal experiences or person</em></strong><em><strong>ality influenced your design ideas?</strong></em><strong><br><br></strong>Ever since I was a kid I was always amazed by everything vintage. My parents were huge hippies, my dad was a drummer and our home was always full of art from his glory years whether that was music, fashion, decor etc. Growing up I wanted to be a singer and music was a big part of our family. I remember sitting with my dad and listening to vinyl records, being totally in love with the album covers. I think about those album covers, the concert posters, the style of that time when I’m creating. I feel like my style allows me to mix my love for music and design in a way that feels authentic to me and my life. <br><strong><br><em>Q:&nbsp;How do you incorporate your personal style into home design projects?</em><br><br></strong>I have two sons so it's hard to make the house my own right now haha. It's full of kids toys and sports equipment. But, I do use rugs to bring my style into the space! I also hang my art on the walls, and I have mostly vintage furniture. I think squeezing in little pieces of you where you can while you're raising young kids is so important! <br><strong><br><em>Q:&nbsp;What drew you to collaborate with our rug brand?<br></em><br></strong>I loved the style of Lany Space rugs! When you all reached out to send me one I knew I had to ask for a collaboration because our styles mesh together so well. The floral rug I got from you all has really helped make my space feel more like me, and I hope that the rugs that I designed can do that for other people! Rugs can change an entire room! <br><strong><br></strong><strong><em>Q:&nbsp;What was your first impression of Lany Space rugs and our style?</em><br><br></strong>I loved it! I could tell that the designs were very art forward. ''Not your mamas rugs''&nbsp;if that makes sense haha. They were very modern, but in a warm vintage way. <br><strong><br><em>Q:&nbsp;Could you share the story or concept behind the collection you designed for us? What inspired the design of this rug collection?</em><br><br></strong>I always say my art has two styles, flowers or space lol. For this collection I leaned into the space side of my style. When I designed my youngest sons nursery I wanted it to be space themed, but not in the traditional ''boy space room''&nbsp;way. I wanted it to be more whimsical, vintage, colorful and fun. These are all rugs I could have used for his room. I was channeling that energy when I made these designs. I wanted them to be able to be used in a kids room, but also a home office or living room. They are spacey but in a more modern and mature way. <br><strong><br><em>Q:&nbsp;Among the pieces in this collection, which design is your favorite, and why?</em><br><br></strong>That's a tough one because I really love them all! I'd have to say the rainbow wave runner. Runners are something that tend to be really dated, because for a long time young people weren't using them as much as the generation before. They were geared towards the order generation who was most likely to buy them. I love seeing funky runners and I can't wait to put this one in my kitchen! I tend to use rainbow waves a lot in my work so that rug feels the most ''me''&nbsp;as well. <br><strong><br><em>Q:&nbsp;If you could sum up this collection in three words, what would they be?</em><br><br></strong>Colorful, vintage, celestial. <strong><br></strong></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-38_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-39_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-40_ pf-heading-1-h2"><i class="sc-czkhzk fzclRt pf-41_ pf-icon-1 pfa pfa-star pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide pf-hide" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>Darra Sargent's Planet Designs for Lany Space</h2></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-42_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-43_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-44_ pf-heading-1-h3"><i class="sc-czkhzk fzclRt pf-45_ pf-icon-1 pfa pfa-star pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide pf-hide" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>Orange/Colorful Disco Planet Rug by Darra Sargent </h3></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-46_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:6;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-47_"><img title="Orange/Colorful Disco Planet Rug by Darra Sargnt" alt="Orange/Colorful Disco Planet Rug by Darra Sargnt" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/files/CCC02157_b131ad38-febb-43f8-900d-ee509201afc1.webp?v=1747973725&width=2048" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/files/CCC02157_b131ad38-febb-43f8-900d-ee509201afc1.webp?v=1747973725&width=375 375w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/fi